# üó∫Ô∏è Science Hub: Master Phase Roadmap v2.0

## Complete Build Sequence to Finished App

---

## Phase 0: Foundation Refactor (In Progress)

**Goal:** Stabilize existing code before scaling

### 0.1 Consolidate gamification (event bus + unified engine)
### 0.2 Create lesson data schema & template system (JSON + renderer)
### 0.3 Build lesson builder UI (internal content creation tool)
### 0.4 Migrate existing 7 lessons to new system
### 0.5 Stabilization & optimization (bug fixes, performance, Lesson 1-3 enhancement)

**Exit Criteria:**
- 8 lessons production-ready (6 migrated + 2 new)
- Zero critical bugs
- Performance validated at 16-lesson scale
- Kyle's workflow unblocked

---

## Phase 1: Content Sprint (Weeks 3-6)

**Goal:** Fill the content gap (8 lessons ‚Üí 18 lessons)

### 1.1 Complete Module 1: Cells (8 lessons total, 6 done, need 2 more)
### 1.2 Complete Module 2: Organisation of Living Things (5 lessons)
### 1.3 Complete Module 5: Heredity (5 lessons)
### 1.4 Build module router (hide empty modules, show "Coming Soon")
### 1.5 Content validation pipeline (schema check + peer review)

**Exit Criteria:** 18 lessons across 3 modules, no empty stubs visible to users

---

## Phase 2: Learning Experience Polish (Weeks 7-9)

**Goal:** Make it feel like a premium app, not a website

### 2.1 Search enhancement (full-text index, filters by module/difficulty)
### 2.2 "Continue where you left off" smart redirect
### 2.3 Study session timer + break reminders
### 2.4 Print-friendly styles for notes
### 2.5 First-time user onboarding (tooltips, progress explanation)

**Exit Criteria:** Student can find any content in <30 seconds, seamless daily use

---

## Phase 3: Gamification Expansion (Weeks 10-12)

**Goal:** Make it addictive (healthy way)

### 3.1 Study plans (customizable schedules, deadlines)
### 3.2 Weak area detection (quiz performance analytics)
### 3.3 Targeted practice mode (review wrong answers)
### 3.4 Social features prep (share progress, study groups architecture)
### 3.5 Push notifications (reminders, streak warnings)

**Exit Criteria:** Student opens app 3+ days/week voluntarily, knows exactly what to study next

---

## Phase 4: Mini-Games & Interactives (Weeks 13-16)

**Goal:** Learning through play, not just reading

### 4.1 Drag-drop cell builder (build prokaryotic/eukaryotic cells)
### 4.2 Process sequencing games (mitosis steps, photosynthesis stages)
### 4.3 Labeling speed challenges (timed diagram labeling)
### 4.4 Matching memory games (terminology + definitions)
### 4.5 Experiment simulator (virtual microscope, pH testing)

**Exit Criteria:** 8+ game types, each lesson has at least 1 interactive element

---

## Phase 5: Backend & Sync (Weeks 17-20)

**Goal:** Cross-device progress, teacher dashboards, data safety

### 5.1 Firebase integration (Auth, Firestore, Hosting)
### 5.2 Cloud sync (progress follows student across devices)
### 5.3 Storage adapter abstraction (seamless LocalStorage ‚Üí Firebase switch)
### 5.4 Teacher dashboard (class progress, weak topics, completion rates)
### 5.5 Data export (PDF progress reports for parents/teachers)

**Exit Criteria:** Student logs in on phone, sees same progress on laptop. Teacher can view class overview.

---

## Phase 6: Advanced Features (Weeks 21-24)

**Goal:** Personalization and smart learning

### 6.1 Adaptive difficulty (lessons adjust based on quiz performance)
### 6.2 Spaced repetition for flashcards (optimal review timing)
### 6.3 AI study coach (suggests what to review, encourages weak areas)
### 6.4 Voice navigation (accessibility + hands-free study)
### 6.5 Dark mode (user preference, saves battery)

**Exit Criteria:** App feels "smart" - knows what student needs before they do

---

## Phase 7: Scale & Content Expansion (Weeks 25-32)

**Goal:** Complete curriculum coverage

### 7.1 HSC Chemistry Module 1-8 (30 lessons)
### 7.2 Year 9-10 Science (Core topics, 20 lessons)
### 7.3 Year 7-8 Science (Foundation, 20 lessons)
### 7.4 Exam preparation mode (HSC past paper integration)
### 7.5 Content versioning (syllabus updates, error corrections)

**Exit Criteria:** 100+ lessons across 3 subjects, covers NSW Science 7-12

---

## Phase 8: Monetization & Sustainability (Weeks 33-36)

**Goal:** Make it a real product, not a project

### 8.1 Premium tier (advanced features, no ads, offline downloads)
### 8.2 School licenses (bulk pricing, admin controls, SSO)
### 8.3 Content marketplace (teachers can create/sell lessons)
### 8.4 Analytics dashboard (usage stats, popular content, drop-off points)
### 8.5 Community features (student forums, study groups, peer tutoring)

**Exit Criteria:** Revenue model working, sustainable development funded, active user community

---

## Phase 9: Platform Expansion (Weeks 37-44)

**Goal:** Beyond NSW, beyond web

### 9.1 National curriculum alignment (VIC, QLD, WA, SA versions)
### 9.2 Native app wrappers (iOS/Android via Capacitor/React Native)
### 9.3 Offline-first architecture (full content sync, no internet required)
### 9.4 Accessibility certification (WCAG AAA, screen reader optimized)
### 9.5 International expansion (UK GCSE, US AP Bio/Chem)

**Exit Criteria:** App store presence, works seamlessly offline, multiple countries

---

## Phase 10: Innovation & Future (Weeks 45+)

**Goal:** Cutting-edge learning technology

### 10.1 AR/VR integration (3D cell exploration, virtual labs)
### 10.2 AI tutor (natural language Q&A, explains any concept)
### 10.3 Predictive analytics (identify at-risk students early)
### 10.4 Gamification 2.0 (leaderboards, competitions, collaborative challenges)
### 10.5 Research partnerships (learning science, efficacy studies)

**Exit Criteria:** Industry-leading educational app, published research on efficacy, 100K+ active users

---

## üìã Phase Gate Rules

### Before starting any phase:
- [ ] Previous phase passed testing specialist approval
- [ ] All critical bugs from previous phase resolved
- [ ] Documentation updated to reflect current state
- [ ] Coder has read and understood specification

### During each phase:
- [ ] No scope creep (features stay in their assigned phase)
- [ ] Mobile-first testing throughout
- [ ] Accessibility maintained (WCAG AA minimum)
- [ ] Performance budget enforced (<500KB per lesson)

### Phase completion criteria:
- [ ] All exit criteria met
- [ ] Testing specialist approval
- [ ] User testing (minimum 3 students, no critical confusion)
- [ ] Documentation updated

---

